'''Torinaruminokami''' (鳥鳴海神, トリナルミ) is a deity appearing in {{ill|Japanese mythology|ja|日本神話}}.

== Overview ==
Torinaruminokami is a deity mentioned in the ''{{ill|Kojiki|ja|古事記}}'' as one of the {{ill|The 17 Generations of Deities|ja|十七世神}} (Tōmarinanayo no Kami). The deity's role and actions are not elaborated beyond the name, which is interpreted to mean "a sea where birds carry spirits and resound."{{Sfn|Nishinomiya|2014|p=381}}

== Genealogy ==
[[File:Ohokuninushi family tree.png|right|thumb|250px|Genealogy of Ōkuninushi (as per the ''Kojiki''). Blue represents male deities, red represents female deities, and yellow represents deities of unknown gender.]]

Torinaruminokami was born to {{ill|Ōkuninushi|ja|大国主神}} and {{ill|Tottorijin|ja|鳥取神}}. The deity married {{ill|Hinateru Nukatabimichioikochini no Kami|ja|日名照額田毘道男伊許知邇神}} and fathered {{ill|Kuninotoshimi no Kami|ja|国忍富神}}.

== Shrines Dedicated ==
* '''Narumi Shrine''' ({{ill|Inuyama|ja|犬山市}}, {{ill|Aichi Prefecture|ja|愛知県}}) - Main enshrined deity.
* '''Ueki Shrine''' ({{ill|Iga|ja|伊賀市}}, {{ill|Mie Prefecture|ja|三重県}}) - Secondary enshrined deity.
* '''Tahika Shrine''' ({{ill|Komono Town|ja|菰野町}}, {{ill|Mie District, Mie Prefecture|ja|三重郡}}, Mie Prefecture) - Merged deity.

