'''Torinarumi-no-Kami''' (鳥鳴海神, トリナルミ, {{lang-en|Torinarumi-no-Kami|12=draft|12=draft}}) is a {{ill|Japanese mythology|ja|日本神話|deity in Japanese mythology=deity in Japanese mythology|lt=deity in Japanese mythology|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Overview == Torinarumi-no-Kami is a deity mentioned in the {{ill|Kojiki|ja|古事記|12=draft|12=draft}} and belongs to the {{ill|17 spirits of the world|simple|user:immanuelle/17 spirits of the world|ja|十七世神|12=draft|12=draft}} (とおまりななよのかみ). This deity is classified as a {{ill|Kunitsukami|ja|国津神|12=draft|12=draft}} and is only described by name in the text. The name is interpreted as "a bird that carries spirits, resonating through the sea"{{Sfn|Nishimiya|2014|p=381}}.
== Genealogy == [[File:Ohokuninushi family tree.png|right|thumb|250px|Genealogy of Ōkuninushi (according to the ''Kojiki''). Blue represents male deities, red female deities, and yellow indicates unknown gender.]] Torinarumi-no-Kami was born from the union of {{ill|Ōkuninushi|ja|大国主神|12=draft|12=draft}} and his wife, {{ill|Tottori-no-Kami|ja|鳥取神|12=draft|12=draft}}, the daughter of {{ill|Yashimajin|ja|八島牟遅能神|1=Yashimamuji|1=Yashimamuji|12=draft|12=draft}}. Torinarumi-no-Kami married {{ill|Hinateri-Nukada-Bichio-Ikochini-no-Kami|ja|日名照額田毘道男伊許知邇神|1=Hinateri-Nukada-Bichio-Ikochini-no-Kami|12=draft|12=draft}} and gave birth to {{ill|Kuninobutomi-no-Kami|ja|国忍富神|1=Kuninotoshimi-no-Kami|1=Kuninotoshimi-no-Kami|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Shrines enshrining Torinarumi-no-Kami == * '''Narumi Shrine''' ({{ill|Inuyama|ja|犬山市|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Aichi Prefecture|ja|愛知県|12=draft|12=draft}}) - Main deity * '''Ueki Shrine''' ({{ill|Iga|ja|伊賀市|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Mie Prefecture|ja|三重県|12=draft|12=draft}}) - Enshrined alongside others * '''Tabika Shrine''' (Komono Town, {{ill|Mie District, Mie Prefecture|ja|三重郡|12=draft|12=draft}}) - Included in a [[Shrine Consolidation Policy|merger]]
*
== Family Tree == {{Eight generations of Izumo}}
== Related articles == * {{ill|Kayanarumi|ja|カヤナルミ|12=draft|12=draft}} - A deity appearing in the ''{{ill|Engishiki|ja|延喜式|12=draft|12=draft}}'' (巻八, ''Izumo Province Norito''), thought to have a connection due to the shared element "Narumi." * {{ill|Nunobutomi-Torinarumi-no-Kami|ja|布忍富鳥鳴海神|1=Nunobutomi-Torinarumi-no-Kami|12=draft|12=draft}} - The thirteenth generation deity among the Completion tier 3]] |ref={{SfnRef|Nishimiya|2014}} |author=[[Kazutami Nishimiya]] 校注 |isbn=978-4-10-620801-0 |series=[[Shinchō Nihon Koten Shūsei]] (new edition)}} [[simple:user:immanuelle/Torinarumi Kami]]
