[[simple:user:immanuelle/Torinarumi Kami]] [[ja:%E9%B3%A5%E9%B3%B4%E6%B5%B7%E7%A5%9E]] [[ja:十七世神|fr|goodbye $1/17 esprits du monde]] [[ja:建速須佐之男命|simple|goodbye $1/Takehaya Susanoo no Mikoto]] [[ja:十七世神]] [[ja:大国主神]] [[ja:国忍富神]] [[ja:国津神]] [[ja:鳥取神]] [[ja:日名照額田毘道男伊許知邇神]] [[ja:古事記]] [[ja:鳥鳴海神]] [[sn:Torinaruminokami]] [[sn:ategory:十七世神]] [[sn:Torinarumi-no-Kami]] [[sn:orinaruminokami]]

{{infobox deity| member_of= {{ill|17 spirits of the world|simple|user:immanuelle/17 spirits of the world|ja|十七世神|qq=draft|qq=draft}} | type = Shinto | not_children = | not_father = | not_consort = | not_mother = |ignore = is one of the {{ill|17 spirits of the world|simple|goodbye $1/17 spirits of the world|en|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. This is a group of Japanese deities ({{ill|Kunitsukami|en}}) that are all in a genealogical relationship descending from {{ill|Susanoo|en|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.goodbye $1 | Name = Torinaruminokami | Generation = {{ill|17 spirits of the world|simple|user:immanuelle/17 spirits of the world|ja|十七世神|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (7th Generation) | Predecessor = {{ill|Ōkuninushi|en}}|Successor = {{ill|Kuninotoshimi-no-Kami|en|qq=draft|qq=draft}} | Divine Order = {{ill|Kunitsukami|en}}|Full Name = 鳥鳴海神 (Torinaruminokami) | Alternate Name= | Other Names = | Divine Rank = | Divine Role = God of Rituals | Mausoleum = | father = {{ill|Ōkuninushi|en|qq=draft|qq=draft}} | mother = {{ill|Tottorijin|en}}|Relatives = | consort = {{ill|Hinateru Nukatabimichioikochini no Kami|en|qq=draft|qq=draft}} | children = {{ill|Kuninotoshimi-no-Kami|en}}|cult_centre = {{Plainlist| * Narumi Shrine * Ueki Shrine * Tahika Shrine|qq=draft|qq=draft}} | Texts = {{ill|Kojiki|en}} }}
'''Torinarumi-no-Kami''' (鳥鳴海神, トリナルミ, {{lang-en|Torinarumi-no-Kami|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) is a {{ill|Japanese mythology|ja|日本神話|deity in Japanese mythology=deity in Japanese mythology|lt=deity in Japanese mythology|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
== Overview == Torinarumi-no-Kami is a deity mentioned in the {{ill|Kojiki|ja|古事記|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and belongs to the {{ill|17 spirits of the world|simple|user:immanuelle/17 spirits of the world|ja|十七世神|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (とおまりななよのかみ). This deity is classified as a {{ill|Kunitsukami|ja|国津神|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and is only described by name in the text. The name is interpreted as "a bird that carries spirits, resonating through the sea"{{Sfn|Nishimiya|2014|p=381}}.
== Genealogy == [[File:Ohokuninushi family tree.png|right|thumb|250px|Genealogy of Ōkuninushi (according to the ''Kojiki''). Blue represents male deities, red female deities, and yellow indicates unknown gender.]] Torinarumi-no-Kami was born from the union of {{ill|Ōkuninushi|ja|大国主神|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and his wife, {{ill|Tottori-no-Kami|ja|鳥取神|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, the daughter of {{ill|Yashimajin|ja|八島牟遅能神|1=Yashimamuji|1=Yashimamuji|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. Torinarumi-no-Kami married {{ill|Hinateri-Nukada-Bichio-Ikochini-no-Kami|ja|日名照額田毘道男伊許知邇神|1=Hinateri-Nukada-Bichio-Ikochini-no-Kami|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and gave birth to {{ill|Kuninobutomi-no-Kami|ja|国忍富神|1=Kuninotoshimi-no-Kami|1=Kuninotoshimi-no-Kami|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
== Shrines enshrining Torinarumi-no-Kami == * '''Narumi Shrine''' ({{ill|Inuyama|ja|犬山市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Aichi Prefecture|ja|愛知県|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) - Main deity * '''Ueki Shrine''' ({{ill|Iga|ja|伊賀市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Mie Prefecture|ja|三重県|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) - Enshrined alongside others * '''Tabika Shrine''' (Komono Town, {{ill|Mie District, Mie Prefecture|ja|三重郡|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) - Included in a [[Shrine Consolidation Policy|merger]]
*
== Family Tree == {{Eight generations of Izumo}}
== Related articles == * {{ill|Kayanarumi|ja|カヤナルミ|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - A deity appearing in the ''{{ill|Engishiki|ja|延喜式|qq=draft|qq=draft}}'' (巻八, ''Izumo Province Norito''), thought to have a connection due to the shared element "Narumi." * {{ill|Nunobutomi-Torinarumi-no-Kami|ja|布忍富鳥鳴海神|1=Nunobutomi-Torinarumi-no-Kami|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - The thirteenth generation deity among the Completion tier 3]] |ref={{SfnRef|Nishimiya|2014}} |author=[[Kazutami Nishimiya]] 校注 |isbn=978-4-10-620801-0 |series=[[Shinchō Nihon Koten Shūsei]] (new edition)}}
