{{afc comment|Wikidata entry (none) Wikidata name: (none) [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 05:31, 12 June 2025 (UTC)}} {{afc comment|Wikidata entry (none) Wikidata name: (none) [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 10:01, 11 June 2025 (UTC)}} {{infobox deity| member_of= {{ill|The 17 Generations of Deities|lt=The 17 Generations of Deities|lt=17 spirits of the world|simple|user:immanuelle/17 spirits of the world|ja|十七世神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/17 spirits of the world|qq=}} | type = Shinto | not_children = | not_father = | not_consort = | not_mother = |ignore = is one of the [[Category:17_spirits_of_the_world]]{{ill|The 17 Generations of Deities|lt=The 17 Generations of Deities|lt=17 spirits of the world|simple|goodbye $1/17 spirits of the world|en|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/17 spirits of the world|qq=}}. This is a group of Japanese deities ({{ill|Kunitsukami|en|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kunitsukami|qq=}}) that are all in a genealogical relationship descending from {{ill|Susanoo-no-Mikoto|lt=Susanoo-no-Mikoto|lt=Susanoo|1=Susanoo-no-Mikoto|en|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Susanoo|13=User:Immanuelle/Susanoo-no-Mikoto|qq=}}.goodbye $1 | Name = Torinaruminokami | Generation = {{ill|The 17 Generations of Deities|lt=The 17 Generations of Deities|lt=17 spirits of the world|simple|user:immanuelle/17 spirits of the world|ja|十七世神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/17 spirits of the world|qq=}} (7th Generation) | Predecessor = {{ill|Ōkuninushi|en|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōkuninushi|qq=}}|Successor = {{ill|Kuninotoshimi-no-Kami|en|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kuninotoshimi-no-Kami|qq=}} | Divine Order = {{ill|Kunitsukami|en|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kunitsukami|qq=}}|Full Name = 鳥鳴海神 (Torinaruminokami) | Alternate Name= | Other Names = | Divine Rank = | Divine Role = God of Rituals | Mausoleum = | father = {{ill|Ōkuninushi|en|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōkuninushi|qq=}} | mother = {{ill|Tottori-no-Kami|lt=Tottori-no-Kami|lt=Tottorijin|en|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tottorijin|qq=}}|Relatives = | consort = {{ill|Hinateri-Nukada-Bichio-Ikochini-no-Kami|lt=Hinateri-Nukada-Bichio-Ikochini-no-Kami|lt=Hinateru Nukatabimichioikochini no Kami|en|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hinateru Nukatabimichioikochini no Kami|qq=}} | children = {{ill|Kuninotoshimi-no-Kami|en|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kuninotoshimi-no-Kami|qq=}}|cult_centre = {{Plainlist| * Narumi Shrine * Ueki Shrine * Tahika Shrine|qq=draft|qq=draft}} | Texts = {{ill|Kojiki|en|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kojiki|qq=}} }}
'''Torinarumi-no-Kami''' (鳥鳴海神, トリナルミ, {{lang-en|Torinarumi-no-Kami|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) is a [[:en:Japanese mythology|deity in Japanese mythology]].
== Overview == Torinarumi-no-Kami is a deity mentioned in the [[:en:Kojiki|Kojiki]] and belongs to the [[Category:17_spirits_of_the_world]]{{ill|The 17 Generations of Deities|lt=The 17 Generations of Deities|lt=17 spirits of the world|simple|user:immanuelle/17 spirits of the world|ja|十七世神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/17 spirits of the world|qq=}} (とおまりななよのかみ). This deity is classified as a {{ill|Kunitsukami|ja|国津神|1=Kunitsukami|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kunitsukami|13=User:Immanuelle/Kunitsukami|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 天津神・国津神|comment=confirming this goes to Kunitsukami|1=Kunitsukami|2=zh|3=國神|4=fr|5=Kunitsukami|6=mni|7=ꯀꯨꯅꯤꯠꯁꯨꯀꯃꯤ}} and is only described by name in the text. The name is interpreted as "a bird that carries spirits, resonating through the sea"{{Sfn|Nishimiya|2014|p=381}}.
== Genealogy == [[File:Ohokuninushi family tree.png|right|thumb|250px|Genealogy of Ōkuninushi (according to the ''Kojiki''). Blue represents male deities, red female deities, and yellow indicates unknown gender.]] Torinarumi-no-Kami was born from the union of {{ill|Ōkuninushi|ja|大国主神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōkuninushi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 大国主}} and his wife, {{ill|Tottori-no-Kami|ja|鳥取神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tottori-no-Kami|qq=}}, the daughter of {{ill|Yashimajin|ja|八島牟遅能神|1=Yashimamuji|1=Yashimamuji|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yashimajin|13=User:Immanuelle/Yashimamuji|qq=}}. Torinarumi-no-Kami married {{ill|Hinateri-Nukada-Bichio-Ikochini-no-Kami|ja|日名照額田毘道男伊許知邇神|1=Hinateri-Nukada-Bichio-Ikochini-no-Kami|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hinateri-Nukada-Bichio-Ikochini-no-Kami|13=User:Immanuelle/Hinateri-Nukada-Bichio-Ikochini-no-Kami|qq=}} and gave birth to {{ill|Kuninobutomi-no-Kami|ja|国忍富神|1=Kuninotoshimi-no-Kami|1=Kuninotoshimi-no-Kami|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kuninobutomi-no-Kami|13=User:Immanuelle/Kuninotoshimi-no-Kami|qq=}}.
== Shrines enshrining Torinarumi-no-Kami == * '''Narumi Shrine''' ([[:en:Inuyama, Aichi|Inuyama]], [[:en:Aichi Prefecture|Aichi Prefecture]]) - Main deity * '''Ueki Shrine''' ([[:en:Iga, Mie|Iga]], [[:en:Mie Prefecture|Mie Prefecture]]) - Enshrined alongside others * '''Tabika Shrine''' (Komono Town, [[:en:Mie District, Mie|Mie District, Mie Prefecture]]) - Included in a [[Shrine Consolidation Policy|merger]]
*
== Family Tree == {{Eight generations of Izumo}}
