== Overview == Torinarumi-no-Kami is a deity mentioned in the [[:en:Kojiki|Kojiki]] and belongs to the [[Category:17_spirits_of_the_world]]{{ill|The 17 Generations of Deities|lt=The 17 Generations of Deities|lt=17 spirits of the world|simple|User:Immanuelle/17 spirits of the world|ja|十七世神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/17 spirits of the world|qq=}} (とおまりななよのかみ). This deity is classified as a {{ill|Kunitsukami|ja|国津神|1=Kunitsukami|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kunitsukami|13=User:Immanuelle/Kunitsukami|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 天津神・国津神|comment=confirming this goes to Kunitsukami|1=Kunitsukami|2=zh|3=國神|4=fr|5=Kunitsukami|6=mni|7=ꯀꯨꯅꯤꯠꯁꯨꯀꯃꯤ}} and is only described by name in the text. The name is interpreted as "a bird that carries spirits, resonating through the sea"{{Sfn|Nishimiya|2014|p=381}}.
== Genealogy == [[File:Ohokuninushi family tree.png|right|thumb|250px|Genealogy of Ōkuninushi (according to the ''Kojiki''). Blue represents male deities, red female deities, and yellow indicates unknown gender.]] Torinarumi-no-Kami was born from the union of {{ill|Ōkuninushi|ja|大国主神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōkuninushi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 大国主}} and his wife, {{ill|Tottori-no-Kami|ja|鳥取神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tottori-no-Kami|qq=}}, the daughter of {{ill|Yashimajin|ja|八島牟遅能神|1=Yashimamuji|1=Yashimamuji|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yashimajin|13=User:Immanuelle/Yashimamuji|qq=}}. Torinarumi-no-Kami married {{ill|Hinateri-Nukada-Bichio-Ikochini-no-Kami|ja|日名照額田毘道男伊許知邇神|1=Hinateri-Nukada-Bichio-Ikochini-no-Kami|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hinateri-Nukada-Bichio-Ikochini-no-Kami|13=User:Immanuelle/Hinateri-Nukada-Bichio-Ikochini-no-Kami|qq=}} and gave birth to {{ill|Kuninobutomi-no-Kami|ja|国忍富神|1=Kuninotoshimi-no-Kami|1=Kuninotoshimi-no-Kami|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kuninobutomi-no-Kami|13=User:Immanuelle/Kuninotoshimi-no-Kami|qq=}}.
